 of viewpoints – conscript, POW, protester and veteran – and is essential reading for anyone interested in Britain’s Cold War past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aKorean War, 1950-1953xForeign public opinion, British. 0aKorean War, 1950-1953zGreat Britain. 7aHISTORY / Military / Korean War.2bisacsh  aCold War.  aKorean War.  aLong Second World War.  aMemory.  aanti-war protest.  acitizenship.  aexperience.  alife-writing.  aselfhood.1 aHuxford, Grace, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611896740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526118967423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526118967/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles